Mr. Palletto bought last week.

30
00:05:39,005 --> 00:05:41,496
I said I'd
deliver it today.

31
00:05:41,574 --> 00:05:44,737
- I think you better come in.
- Sure.

32
00:06:02,995 --> 00:06:06,590
You want me to believe
my dad bought that?

33
00:06:06,666 --> 00:06:09,533
Oh, it was your father?
I-I'm sorry. Eh, well, maybe...

34
00:06:09,602 --> 00:06:12,867
Maybe this is not
the right moment, but yeah.

35
00:06:12,939 --> 00:06:15,430
Last Monday
at my gallery.

36
00:06:15,508 --> 00:06:19,308
That's strange.
Last Monday Dad was in a hospital.

37
00:06:21,614 --> 00:06:23,878
- Did I say "last Monday"?
- Mm-hmm.

38
00:06:23,950 --> 00:06:28,614
Maybe... maybe it was
two Mondays ago.

39
00:06:28,688 --> 00:06:32,624
All I know is it was
definitely a Monday.

40
00:06:32,692 --> 00:06:35,820
What's definite is you're
a son of a bitch...

41
00:06:35,895 --> 00:06:37,829
with no respect
for a dead man...

42
00:06:37,897 --> 00:06:40,388
or his family's
suffering.

43
00:06:42,135 --> 00:06:44,399
But you're lucky.

44
00:06:44,470 --> 00:06:47,633
I'm going to help you understand
what suffering is.

45
00:06:52,612 --> 00:06:57,242
Eh... I-I-I can come back
another time.

46
00:06:58,718 --> 00:07:01,551
My father hated
modern art.

47
00:07:01,621 --> 00:07:04,556
He thought the people
who made it were pansies...

48
00:07:05,925 --> 00:07:09,554
and the people
who bought it were suckers.

49
00:07:09,629 --> 00:07:11,722
But they love it.

50
00:07:15,768 --> 00:07:17,998
When they get through
with you...

51
00:07:18,070 --> 00:07:21,335
your face is gonna look
like a Picasso.

52
00:07:21,407 --> 00:07:23,341
Wait, wait, wait.

53
00:07:23,409 --> 00:07:27,505
Maybe this is all
a big misunderstanding.

54
00:07:27,580 --> 00:07:30,515
What did you say
your father's name was?

55
00:08:09,922 --> 00:08:12,516
Let me in.

56
00:08:23,402 --> 00:08:27,998
- I'm sorry, Mama.
- Thank you. Thank you, dear.

57
00:08:31,143 --> 00:08:34,010
Thanks for coming,
Betty.

58
00:08:34,080 --> 00:08:36,014
Good-bye, Gene.

59
00:08:37,884 --> 00:08:41,115
You have my
deepest sympathy.

60
00:08:41,187 --> 00:08:43,781
No. You have mine.

61
00:08:43,856 --> 00:08:46,484
Oh.

62
00:08:48,728 --> 00:08:51,629
I hope time heals all your...

63
