- You're pushing it, pal.
- Pain.

64
00:09:57,964 --> 00:10:00,660
Maria, take care
of Mama.

65
00:10:02,134 --> 00:10:05,103
<i>Betty. Betty.
We need to talk.</i>

66
00:10:05,171 --> 00:10:09,403
<i>I have nothing to say to you, Gene. I
only came out of respect for your father.</i>

67
00:10:09,475 --> 00:10:11,443
Well, Betty, look.
I'm in bad shape.

68
00:10:11,510 --> 00:10:15,105
I'm at home crying my eyes out,
and you're out having a good time.

69
00:10:15,181 --> 00:10:18,548
I'd be having a better time if you
didn't follow me everywhere I went.

70
00:10:18,618 --> 00:10:21,917
You know the happiest day
of my father's life?

71
00:10:21,988 --> 00:10:24,218
The day you and I
got married.

72
00:10:24,290 --> 00:10:26,554
- You know the happiest day of my life?
- What?

73
00:10:26,626 --> 00:10:29,026
The day we got divorced.

74
00:10:29,095 --> 00:10:31,586
- Now get out of my way and leave me alone, you big bully.
- Ooh. Ow.

75
00:10:31,664 --> 00:10:34,599
Betty, Betty.
I'm seeing Dr. Huffeyer.

76
00:10:34,667 --> 00:10:38,967
Oh, great.
That's just great.

77
00:10:39,038 --> 00:10:42,838
Out of all the shrinks in Miami,
you have to go see mine?

78
00:10:42,908 --> 00:10:45,433
Well, I'm not gonna see him anymore because
I don't want to share anything with you...

79
00:10:45,511 --> 00:10:48,878
- not even this planet!
- He's helping me change.

80
00:10:50,950 --> 00:10:53,919
- I'm channeling all my anger
into some positive crap.

81
00:10:53,986 --> 00:10:57,114
Listen to me, damn it!
I've changed! Ow!

82
00:10:59,725 --> 00:11:02,387
I love you!

83
00:11:55,815 --> 00:11:58,648
<i>You can come out now.</i>

84
00:12:01,687 --> 00:12:03,712
- Thanks.
- You're welcome.

85
00:12:03,789 --> 00:12:07,555
That was exciting,
with those big lugs looking for you...

86
00:12:07,626 --> 00:12:11,562
and Gene standing there
not knowing you were in the back seat.

87
00:12:11,630 --> 00:12:14,326
I had a hunch something great
was gonna happen today.

88
00:12:14,400 --> 00:12:16,891
<i>- It did. I'm still alive.
- Yeah.</i>

89
00:12:19,438 --> 00:12:23,374
- Sorry.
- For now. Thanks to you.

90
00:12:25,010 --> 00:12:27,535
I'm Betty.
Betty Kerner.

91
00:12:27,613 --> 00:12:29,911
- Art Dodge.
- It's really nice to meet you, Art.

92
00:12:29,982 --> 00:12:34,681
<i>Same here, Betty.</i>

93
00:12:36,122 --> 00:12:38,920
I guess you are not
going downtown, right?

94
00:12:38,991 --> 00:12:41,585
Uh-uh.

95
00:13:29,475 --> 00:13:31,568
Let me see if you got this right.

96
00:13:31,644 --> 00:13:33,578
<i>- Arriba.
- Arriba.</i>

97
00:13:33,646 --> 00:13:35,580
<i>- Abajo.
- Abajo.</i>

98
00:13:35,648 --> 00:13:38,242
<i>- Al centro.
- Al centro.</i>

99
00:13:38,317 --> 00:13:40,649
<i>- Por dentro.
- Por dentro.</i>

100
00:13:44,356 --> 00:13:46,290
Mmm.

101
00:13:48,294 --> 00:13:51,457
I'm loaded.
Um, what about you?

102
00:13:51,530 --> 00:13:53,589
No.

103
00:13:53,666 --> 00:13:56,760
No, I cry too much.
Don't you ever cry?

104
00:13:56,836 --> 00:14:00,932
Oh, yeah, sure I do. Whenever I
pay taxes, which isn't often anyway.

105
00:14:01,006 --> 00:14:03,338
- You're crazy.
- So are you.

106
00:14:04,410 --> 00:14:06,344
A match made in heaven.

107
00:14:11,217 --> 00:14:14,983
A very long,
pretty blond eyelash.

108
00:14:15,054 --> 00:14:17,488
- Take it with your finger.
- Yeah.

109
00:14:17,556 --> 00:14:20,047
- Okay.
- Make a wish.

110
00:14:22,094 --> 00:14:24,153
- Okay.
- Blow it away.

111
00:14:29,368 --> 00:14:33,634
<i>Who is it?</i>

112
00:14:33,706 --> 00:14:35,640
<i>It's Ellen, darling. Open up.</i>

113
00:14:35,708 --> 00:14:38,973
Oh, gee, in a second.
Just...

114
00:14:39,044 --> 00:14:41,274
<i>Oof!</i>

115
00:14:43,215 --> 00:14:44,807
Oh. Ohh!

116
00:14:52,524 --> 00:14:55,357
I was right.

117
00:14:57,496 --> 00:15:00,727
A match made in heaven.

118
00:15:31,163 --> 00:15:33,495
Hey, that's
Betty Kerner.

119
00:15:33,565 --> 00:15:36,659
And who's that bimbo
with her?

120
00:15:36,735 --> 00:15:38,669
Let's check it out.

121
00:15:38,737 --> 00:15:40,671
Hmm.

122
00:15:40,739 --> 00:15:44,197
They say that the
third time is the charm.

123
00:15:44,276 --> 00:15:46,244
Third what?

124
00:15:46,312 --> 00:15:48,746
- Marriage.
- Oh.

125
00:15:48,814 --> 00:15:52,773
Who was the first?

126
00:15:52,851 --> 00:15:54,682
Gene.

127
00:15:54,753 --> 00:15:56,687
- Who was the second?
- Gene.

128
00:15:56,755 --> 00:15:59,690
You married that guy
twice?

129
00:15:59,758 --> 00:16:02,591
Now ask me who's
gonna be the third.

130
00:16:02,661 --> 00:16:05,858
Miss Kerner. Hey, Miss Kerner,
who's your new friend?

131
00:16:05,931 --> 00:16:08,900
- Eh...
- My fiancé.

132
00:16:47,806 --> 00:16:50,639
Cool.

133
00:17:16,035 --> 00:17:18,503
One, two, three!

134
00:17:18,570 --> 00:17:20,595
<i>Aah!</i>

135
00:17:23,342 --> 00:17:27,278
Boom, boom!
Can you guess what I am thinking?

136
00:17:35,354 --> 00:17:37,288
Can you guess
what I'm thinking?

137
00:17:37,356 --> 00:17:39,620
I'm sorry.

138
00:17:39,691 --> 00:17:43,218
I'm... I'm... I'm sorry.
I-I-I thought that...

139
00:17:43,295 --> 00:17:45,490
You can go out
the same way you came in.

140
00:17:45,564 --> 00:17:49,261
Sure. Uh...
I'm sorry.

141
00:17:49,334 --> 00:17:52,735
<i>Wild guess,
but are these yours?</i>

142
00:17:54,073 --> 00:17:56,268
Yes.

143
00:17:56,341 --> 00:17:58,275
Sorry.

144
00:18:01,980 --> 00:18:04,915
- I'm sorry.
- I know. Now try "good-bye."

145
00:18:04,983 --> 00:18:07,508
Good-bye.

146
00:18:11,890 --> 00:18:13,824
<i>Oh, Dios.</i>

147
00:18:13,892 --> 00:18:16,861
<i>But I have to have it fitted tomorrow.</i>

148
00:18:16,929 --> 00:18:19,056
<i>Ciao.</i>

149
00:18:19,131 --> 00:18:22,191
<i>- How long have you known him?
- Seems like forever.</i>

150
00:18:22,267 --> 00:18:24,827
<i>Oh, less than
24 hours then.</i>

151
00:18:24,903 --> 00:18:28,771
Oh, yes, Hopper.
Of course you can be the flower dog.

152
00:18:28,841 --> 00:18:31,901
<i>Right?</i>

153
00:18:31,977 --> 00:18:36,141
<i>So do I get a new bridesmaid's getup, or should
I just put some more miles on the old one?</i>

154
00:18:38,217 --> 00:18:40,151
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

155
00:18:40,219 --> 00:18:44,747
<i>- You've met my sister Liz already.
- Yeah.</i>

156
00:18:44,823 --> 00:18:47,291
<i>Lay down, now.</i>

157
00:18:47,359 --> 00:18:50,886
Hello?

158
00:18:50,963 --> 00:18:55,627
No, no, no, the invitations should read
"The Honorable Art Dodge," don't you think?

159
00:18:55,701 --> 00:18:58,499
- The invitations?
- Yeah. Engraved.

160
00:18:58,570 --> 00:19:00,800
And they should be
in the mail by Tuesday.

161
00:19:00,873 --> 00:19:03,205
Okay. Ciao.
Fantastic. Bye.

162
00:19:03,275 --> 00:19:06,711
- Betty, can I talk to you alone?
- Yeah, in one second.

163
00:19:06,778 --> 00:19:09,144
In one second.

164
00:19:10,482 --> 00:19:12,507
Father Larrabee.

165
00:19:12,584 --> 00:19:14,814
He's on the golf course?

166
00:19:14,887 --> 00:19:18,823
<i>- Wow, you hooked yourself the big one, didn't you?
- Do you have a cellular number?</i>

167
00:19:18,891 --> 00:19:22,054
This must go way beyond
your wildest little gigolo dreams.

168
00:19:22,127 --> 00:19:25,563
<i>Okay. Thanks.
Isn't he adorable?</i>

169
00:19:25,631 --> 00:19:28,794
- Yeah.
- Betty, we need to talk.

170
00:19:28,867 --> 00:19:31,927
- Wait.
- What about? Your allowance?

171
00:19:32,004 --> 00:19:34,097
<i>- Father Larrabee, it's Betty.
- Look...</i>

172
00:19:34,173 --> 00:19:37,768
<i>- I don't need to. I've seen enough.
- It's good? Great.</i>

173
00:19:37,843 --> 00:19:41,370
No, no. He's a different one.

174
00:19:41,446 --> 00:19:44,438
Yes, but he's wonderful,
and you'll love him.

175
00:19:44,516 --> 00:19:47,110
<i>I'll talk to you soon.
Bye.</i>

176
00:19:47,186 --> 00:19:50,587
So how does
the third sound?

177
00:19:50,656 --> 00:19:53,420
It's my birthday.
I'll be 33.

178
00:19:53,492 --> 00:19:58,225
<i>It's my third wedding,
and three is my lucky number.</i>

179
00:19:58,297 --> 00:20:01,164
- Great. Great.
- Yes?

180
00:20:01,233 --> 00:20:05,693
- Eh, I've got to go to work.
- It has a job. How refreshing.

181
00:20:07,673 --> 00:20:10,039
<i>- Gotta go. Bye.
- Have a good day.</i>

182
00:20:10,108 --> 00:20:13,202
Come on, buddy.
Come on, boy.

183
00:20:13,278 --> 00:20:17,237
- I don't think she likes me.
- Oh, don't listen to her.

184
00:20:17,316 --> 00:20:22,481
She's been involved with this guy who's a
married man. It's been a really bad deal.

185
00:20:31,496 --> 00:20:35,762
<i>I see congratulations
are in order.</i>

186
00:20:35,834 --> 00:20:39,668
