It's like a big misunderstanding.

187
00:20:39,738 --> 00:20:42,434
<i>- Okay?
- Oh, so, like, you've explained it to her...</i>

188
00:20:42,507 --> 00:20:44,771
and everything's all
straightened out for ya?

189
00:20:44,843 --> 00:20:48,108
<i>- Well, no, not exactly.
- Uh-huh.</i>

190
00:20:48,180 --> 00:20:50,774
<i>Everything is totally
high or low with her.</i>

191
00:20:50,849 --> 00:20:53,943
She'll be down on me soon enough,
and then it'll all be over.

192
00:20:54,019 --> 00:20:56,817
Trust me. She's a girl
with big extremes.

193
00:20:56,888 --> 00:21:00,255
So I see.
Manny's in there.

194
00:21:00,325 --> 00:21:02,259
He's been in there
for an hour.

195
00:21:02,327 --> 00:21:05,057
- Come on, Gloria.
- What do you want me to do?

196
00:21:05,130 --> 00:21:07,928
I feel sorry for the guy.
We owe him for two paintings.

197
00:21:08,000 --> 00:21:12,061
Is the I RS in there?
Maybe you feel sorry for everyone I owe.

198
00:21:12,137 --> 00:21:16,301
Everyone? No.
I don't believe in self-pity.

199
00:21:17,943 --> 00:21:21,208
Manny. Just the man
I wanted to see.

200
00:21:21,280 --> 00:21:24,738
- Art.
- What's that?

201
00:21:24,816 --> 00:21:29,515
Wow!
This is terrific.

202
00:21:29,588 --> 00:21:32,148
- I can sell it in a week.
- Oh, no, no, no, no, no.

203
00:21:32,224 --> 00:21:34,419
- It's been hanging here for three months.
- Really?

204
00:21:34,493 --> 00:21:37,189
I'm taking them all home.

205
00:21:37,262 --> 00:21:39,924
<i>- Art?
- Yeah?</i>

206
00:21:39,998 --> 00:21:42,432
You still haven't paid me
for the last two.

207
00:21:42,501 --> 00:21:45,834
Wha...
You should thank me.

208
00:21:45,904 --> 00:21:49,931
Manny,
if Vincent van Gogh...

209
00:21:50,008 --> 00:21:52,533
had been paid
for his paintings...

210
00:21:52,611 --> 00:21:55,341
they would be worthless
today.

211
00:21:55,414 --> 00:21:59,111
You shouldn't be thinking about money.
You're an artist.

212
00:21:59,184 --> 00:22:02,881
You're a real one.
I can see that in your eyes.

213
00:22:02,954 --> 00:22:06,720
Huh? Yeah, yeah!
Believe me. Yeah.

214
00:22:08,093 --> 00:22:10,618
You know...
You know, Manny...

215
00:22:10,696 --> 00:22:14,063
Manny, go home and paint.

216
00:22:14,132 --> 00:22:17,624
Paint, Manny, paint.
Come on. Eh?

217
00:22:17,703 --> 00:22:20,900
- Yeah, yeah. Maybe you're right.
- Yeah, I'm right.

218
00:22:20,972 --> 00:22:23,907
- But what about you?
- What about me? What? What?

219
00:22:23,975 --> 00:22:28,275
- You were good.
- Good is the same as bad.

220
00:22:28,347 --> 00:22:30,713
It has to be brilliant.

221
00:22:31,850 --> 00:22:34,751
Yeah. So why is it
hanging on your wall?

222
00:22:36,455 --> 00:22:39,618
Well, it's just, uh...

223
00:22:39,691 --> 00:22:42,717
reminding me not
to pick up a brush again.

224
00:22:42,794 --> 00:22:46,855
Yeah. You like it?
Take it.

225
00:22:46,932 --> 00:22:51,926
It's yours. Consider it an advance
on what I owe you.

226
00:22:52,003 --> 00:22:53,937
Huh?

227
00:22:57,008 --> 00:22:59,602
- I don't know what to say.
- Don't say anything.

228
00:22:59,678 --> 00:23:03,205
Real artists
don't need words.

229
00:23:05,150 --> 00:23:07,084
Eh?

230
00:23:08,420 --> 00:23:10,752
All right.

231
00:23:10,822 --> 00:23:13,382
Good-bye.
See you, huh?

232
00:23:29,574 --> 00:23:32,338
- What's Manny doing with your painting?
- I'm redecorating.

233
00:23:33,412 --> 00:23:36,404
It was the nicest thing
in here.

234
00:23:48,059 --> 00:23:50,653
Excuse me, miss.

